<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd135505b-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s1704"><num value="1704">§ 1704.</num><heading> Authority to issue regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may issue such regulations, including regulations prescribing definitions, as may be necessary for the exercise of the authorities granted by this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd135505c-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/223/tII/s205">Pub. L. 95–223, title II, § 205</ref>, <date date="1977-12-28">Dec. 28, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/1628">91 Stat. 1628</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
